## {{ rule.title }}

[Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) lines 33-37 reconcile **total tax** against **total payments** (estimated payments + withholding). The [Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) instructions describe two outcomes:

- **Line 35a (refund)** when payments exceed total tax — the amount can be sent to a bank account on [Form 8888](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-8888) or carried forward.
- **Line 37 (amount you owe)** when total tax exceeds payments — paid by the April due date to avoid [§ 6651](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section6651&num=0&edition=prelim) / [§ 6654](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section6654&num=0&edition=prelim) penalties.

For 2025:

- Total tax with treaty re-sourcing (regular tax minus allowed FTC plus NIIT): **{{ rule.inputs_by_key["us.tax.total_tax_with_treaty_resourcing_usd"].value | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Estimated payment already made: **{{ rule.inputs_by_key["us.payments.estimated_payment_usd"].value | money(currency="USD") }}**

Outcome:

- **Refund (line 35a)**: **{{ rule.outputs[0].value | money(currency="USD") }}**
- **Amount owed (line 37)**: **{{ rule.outputs[1].value | money(currency="USD") }}**

(Exactly one of those two will be non-zero.)

